<br>
At the very close of the day as I was medding in Rivervale, a member of the big uberguild on the server inspects me, and a few moments later hands me a Brown Chitin Protector.<br>
<br>
Now, I THINK the Ulthork-hide has the BCP beat in AC by a point or two, and is also lighter.  While I appreciate the gesture of just giving me something like this, and barring fashion, is there a reason I should wear it?<br>
<br>
 <p>Daeddwin Proudfoot<br>
35th (FINALLY) Level Lowbie Halfling Druid<br>
Officer of <i>Spirit of Norrath</i><br>
<b>Lanys T'yvl</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/16/01 2:31:15 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/Aerynn?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ulthork Hide vs BcP?</span><hr size=1> Hit Points and Charisma.  <br>
<br>
The Ulthork Tunic has a negative 35 hit points on it, and decreases charisma by 5.  If I am doing any charming or am in a situation where I am rarely OOM, I use the BCP. (Along with the stamina on it, I get about 50 more hit points and have needed every last one a couple times.)  <br>
<br>
Most of the time I'm using the Ulthork to get the additional three wisdom and the 35 mana on it.  It depends on what I'm hunting and what kind of group I'm in.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps you...<br>
<br>
Aerynn<br>
44th Level Wood Elf Druid<br>
Residing on Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udaeddwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeddwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/16/01 2:45:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ulthork Hide vs BcP?</span><hr size=1> *nod*  The -35 hit points is one of the things I was a little worried about... but I spend most of my time grouping, and ideally not getting hit.<br>
<br>
As for the charisma... I'm a Halfling.  ;)  I'm only down about 2 points of charisma total, thanks to my acolyte's anklet, but if I wore the BCP, my cha would still only be 53 or so.<br>
<br>
 <p>Daeddwin Proudfoot<br>
35th (FINALLY) Level Lowbie Halfling Druid<br>
Officer of <i>Spirit of Norrath</i><br>
<b>Lanys T'yvl</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueqgryffindor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQGryffindor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/17/01 4:39:18 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/eqbrimztone/eqgryffindor.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ulthork Hide vs BcP?</span><hr size=1> I would wear the Ulthork for the +3wis, and the look of the ulthork. The BCP on the other is good but i would wear the ulthork for the +3wis.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><center><img src="http://www.geocities.com/eqbrimztone/eqgryffindor2.jpg"><br><font size=4 color=black>Gryffindor Shadowjumpr'<br>
14 Druid Pround Member of Trinnity <br></font>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujabotik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jabotik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/01 11:00:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ulthork Hide vs BcP?</span><hr size=1> Dump the bcp and get cured tizmak. Easier to get (and cheaper than bcp), has 15ac 7sv magic, weight 3.0 with no neg stats. Quad with ulthork, group with tizmak.<br>
<br>
Jabo <p>Guarding with my life..oh splendid one</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukalinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/01 11:09:34 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/Kalinn?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ulthork Hide vs BcP?</span><hr size=1> if you do much porcupining, which is still viable at your level, stick with the bcp.  the ulthork may seem to have more ac, 13 vs 12, but the bcp has 9 sta and 9 agi.  the 9 agi will make the total ac from the bcp higher than the ulthork, and the 9 sta will add a few hp as well (i get about 26hp out of 9 sta). <p>-K<br><br>
The right to do something doesn't mean that doing it is right. -William Safire
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udunedainoakenshield.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DunedainOakenshield</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/20/01 12:36:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ulthork Hide vs BcP?</span><hr size=1> Most of you are forgetting the plus 35 mana.  That at least takes it to  5 wis or even 6.  At that level you can exchange out some other gear to get more AC if you wish.  I good item to get would be the Bracers of Hammerfall.  2 VERY easy items to get in SS, better ac then RMBs and add 25hp each.  Just 3 wis each but made up for by the Tunic.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3130.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3127.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.emailToFriend?topicID=3114.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.threadControl?topicID=3114.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3114.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3114.topic>Unsu